==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ligate
<hw>Li"gate</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧"g⟦amac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ligatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>ligare</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To tie with a ligature; to bind around; to bandage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Molecular biology)</fld> <def>To concatenate two
strands of (nucleic acid, usually DNA), in an end-to-end fashion, using
a ligase.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ligation</ent>⟦br⟧
